svg.title: Plan C shows a map of St. Mary Mead; the compass points are set as an X, with North pointing to the upper left. A long street runs from left to right: at the left end is the train station opposite Laurence Reddy’s cottage. Moving right on the upper side of this street are shops and small houses before a crossroads, with the church on one corner, and the Blue Boar on the far corner. On the lower side of the street, Mrs. Lestrange’s cottage is at the corner of lane; on the opposite corner there are more shops, then come the homes of Miss Marple, Miss Hartnell, and Miss Wetherby, with Miss Wetherby’s opposite the church. Each house is bounded by the main street on one side, and the Vicarage lane on the other. The map shows Dr. Haydock’s house immediately next door to Miss Marple’s, behind the shops and above the Vicarage, while Mrs. Price Ridley’s home is on the far side of and below the Vicarage.
